    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Creskeld Hall | Otley</placeName>
                    <date>April 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. 1871.</date>
                    <salute>Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>A friend of ours, Col: le Couteur of Jersey, whose tastes &amp; pursuits are similar to your own, and who takes the greatest interest in your writings &amp; researches, has written to us, to request an introduction, and mentioning, that he has some further information which he thinks will amuse you.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>With our kind regards, | Believe me | Y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. very truly | Charlotte M. C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">No letter from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2848.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">John Le Couteur</ref> has been found, but see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7661A.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to John Le Couteur, 6 April [1871]</ref>. Charlotte’s husband was <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1223.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Francis Rhodes Darwin</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
    </body>
